 and goals  Build your resume with valuable professional experience  Develop career readiness skills and competencies  Connect with employers and establish a network of contacts  Get ahead of the competition in landing a full-time job after graduation        Other JLD services available to all Students    Networking /Hiring Opportunities at Career Fairs and Employer Information Booths  Career Development Workshops  Drop-In Advising        JLD Eligibility Requirements    Must be a UIC Student registered for at least 6 credit hours  Cannot be a graduating senior in your last semester; Graduate students are eligible  U.S. Citizens or Permanent Residents only        How to Register   Fill out a JLD Interest Form online; once your eligibility has been verified, we will contact you to set up an appointment with the JLD Coordinator.  Click HERE for the JLD Interest Form.  Questions? Contact the JLD Coordinator, Sandy Le, at sle4@uic.edu or 312-996-3130.          Students    Back to main content           Job Listings    On Campus Job Requirements     Employment Eligibility Verification      Job Location & Development    Student FAQs                  UIC Logo        Student Employment         Quick Links    UIC Career Services    UIC Careers      For Students    Job Listings    JLD Program      For Departments    Forms    Job Descriptions    Student Wage Plan        Footer Menu    Students    Departments    UIC Careers    UIC Career Services         Contact   Suite 2100 1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, Illinois 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3130  Fax: (312) 413-7944  studentjobs@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy 